Iran will not renegotiate a 2015 nuclear deal with major powers, Iran’s foreign minister said on Thursday, as a deadline set by U.S. President Donald Trump for Europeans to “fix” the deal loomed. “Iran will not renegotiate what was agreed years ago and has been implemented ... also we will reject any ratification of it,” Mohammad Javad Zarif said in a message posted on YouTube. ALSO READ:

